-- Saudi Arabia Held Talks With Companies to Build Renewable-Energy City
-- B y   G l e n   C a r e y
-- 2010-10-04T10:09:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-04/saudi-arabia-held-talks-with-companies-to-build-renewable-energy-city.html
Saudi arabia, the Arab world’s
biggest economy, has held talks with international companies to
build the kingdom’s first nuclear and renewable energy city,
said Khalid al-Sulaiman, vice-president for renewable energy at
King Abdullah City for Atomic and Renewable Energy.  “We have engaged the expertise and thinking of 14 of the
best architectural and design houses,” al-Sulaiman said in
Jeddah today. Of these eight are from Saudi Arabia, and the rest
from Asia, Europe and North America, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Glen Carey in Dubai at 
